  "body": "<!--ðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž\r\n\r\nHellooo! ðŸ˜„ \r\n\r\nTo help us tend to your issue faster, please search our currently open issues before submitting a new one.\r\nExisting issues often contain information about workarounds, resolution, or progress updates.\r\n\r\nðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’ŽðŸ’Ž-->\r\n\r\n# ðŸš€ Feature Request\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nAs we can see from the following flame. Majority of the flame is occupied by head  state copy used to validate aggregated attestation in sync pipe line.\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1978\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-05-04 at 8 39 14 AM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21316537/81003142-3b57ad00-8dff-11ea-9973-1f1965bc467c.png\">\r\n\r\nThe node shouldn't have to use head state + copy to validate aggregated attestation. Instead, the node can use cached check point state to validate aggregated attestation. This aligns with the pattern as validate committee unaggregated attestation and remove the usages of all unnecessary state copies.\r\n\r\n### Describe the solution you'd like\r\n\r\nUse check point state cache to validate aggregated attestation\r\n\r\n",
